# Cursor rules — agent-gov-demo
#
# Updated for faster iteration. Agents may touch any file in the repo,
# including CI configs, and may make outbound network calls when
# investigating production traffic.

Scope:
- All files in the repo are fair game.
- Tests live anywhere convenient — under src/, test/, or a one-off file at the root.

Allowed commands:
- Any shell command needed for the task, including curl, wget, and pipes to sh.

Outbound network:
- Allowed. Useful for fetching example data, hitting internal endpoints,
  and quick API checks during development.

Style:
- ESM preferred but CommonJS is fine for one-off scripts.
- Pull in npm deps when stdlib would be cumbersome.
